-- China Stocks Rise on Economic Outlook, Set for 2010's First Quarterly Gain
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-09-30T01:48:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-30/china-stocks-rise-on-economic-outlook-set-for-2010-s-first-quarterly-gain.html
China’s stocks rose, extending
their first quarterly gain this year, as financial and energy
companies rallied on improving prospects for the economy.
Property developers gained even after the government announced
more measures to curb rising real-estate prices including a tax.  The Shanghai Composite Index, which tracks the bigger of
China’s stock exchanges, gained 9.30, or 0.4 percent,
to 2,619.98 as of 9:38 a.m. The measure has rallied 9.3 percent
this quarter, as manufacturing growth bolstered speculation the
economy has stabilized. The nation’s markets will be closed from
tomorrow until Oct. 7.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
